pwd - print working directory
ls - to list files and folders
cd - move to the path
cd .. - move back
cd / - move to root
cat - view file
vi - edit file
rm - remove file
cp - copy file
mv - move file
mkdir - make directory
rmditr - remove empty directory
rm -r - remove diretory will files
man - manual command
clear 
ln -s - to create a link for files


To search in a file
-------------------
vi filename
/search keyword
n - to move to the next word
esc - to search another word


To search and replace 
--------------------
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DikkZpayGeY&ab_channel=HWDsouthCODEHWDsouthCODE
:%s/oldword/newword

vi command
--------------------
i - move to insert mode
u - to undo the last change
esc - move to command mode
:wq - save and quit

grep command
--------------------
grep "word" file.txt
-i to ignore case


